50|$|Among migratory birds, the ruddy {{turnstone}} (Arenaria interpres), sanderling (Calidris alba), <b>bristle-thighed</b> <b>curlew</b> (Numenius tahitiensis), Pacific golden plover (Pluvialis fulva), and grey-tailed (Tringa brevipes) and wandering tattlers (T. incana) use Teeraina as stopover location or winter quarters {{on a regular}} basis. Other shorebirds, gulls, and occasionally ducks of North American and East Asian species may occur as vagrants.|$|E
